Sentencas: Rare earth doped strontium cobaltite (Sr1-xRxCoO3-delta where R is rare earth element like cerium (Ce) (x = 0.0, 0.025)) was synthesized by a composite-mediated hydrothermal method (CMHM).
Titulo: Structural Dependence of Conductivity in Rare Earth Doped Strontium Cobaltite Nanoparticles

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction (XRD) was done to study the structural properties such as crystal structure, crystallite size, lattice constants and phase purity of the samples.
Titulo: Structural Dependence of Conductivity in Rare Earth Doped Strontium Cobaltite Nanoparticles

Sentencas: Phase transformation from monoclinic to the hexagonal structure was observed with heat treatment.
Titulo: Structural Dependence of Conductivity in Rare Earth Doped Strontium Cobaltite Nanoparticles

Sentencas: DC electrical conductivity was studied as a function of temperature in the range from room temperature to 430 degrees C.
Titulo: Structural Dependence of Conductivity in Rare Earth Doped Strontium Cobaltite Nanoparticles

Sentencas: It was observed that DC electrical conductivity increased with increase in temperature and was explained by a hopping model.
Titulo: Structural Dependence of Conductivity in Rare Earth Doped Strontium Cobaltite Nanoparticles

Sentencas: Impedance was measured as a function of temperature (30-600 degrees C) at the frequency of 1 MHz.
Titulo: Structural Dependence of Conductivity in Rare Earth Doped Strontium Cobaltite Nanoparticles

Sentencas: Different parameters were correlated to study the conductivity mechanism.
Titulo: Structural Dependence of Conductivity in Rare Earth Doped Strontium Cobaltite Nanoparticles

Sentencas: The prepared samples are one of the suitable candidates for the cathode of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (ITSOFCs).
Titulo: Structural Dependence of Conductivity in Rare Earth Doped Strontium Cobaltite Nanoparticles
